  "prompt": "How can I play a good safety in a snooker game?",
  "response": "To play a good safety in snooker, consider these tips:\n\n1. Position control\n- Block opponent's path to target balls\n- Leave the cue ball in a difficult position\n- Minimize opponent's scoring opportunities\n\n2. Defensive techniques\n- Hide the cue ball behind other balls\n- Place balls in tight clusters\n- Use cushions to create complex angles\n\n3. Strategic ball placement\n- Place cue ball near or behind other balls\n- Ensure opponent cannot directly hit their desired ball\n- Create challenging angles for your opponent\n\n4. Key skills\n- Accurate positional control\n- Understanding of angles and ball physics\n- Good spin and cushion knowledge\n\n5. Specific safety shots\n- Stun shot\n- Controlled spin shots\n- Kiss-bank safety shots\n\n6. Practice\n- Study professional players' techniques\n- Practice different safety scenarios\n- Develop spatial awareness and precision\n\n7. Mental approach\n- Stay calm and patient\n- Think several shots ahead\n- Anticipate opponent's potential responses\n\n8. Table awareness\n- Know the positions of all balls\n- Understand potential scoring and safety opportunities\n- Plan multiple potential outcomes\n\nConsistent practice and strategic thinking are crucial to developing strong safety play in snooker.",
